AILANG Redis Server - Build Guide
Prerequisites

AILANG compiler (Python 3.x)
Linux/WSL environment
gcc (for AILANG compiler backend)

Quick Start
bash# 1. Clone or download the AILANG compiler
git clone [ailang-repo-url]
cd ailang

# 2. Place files in correct locations
# - redis_server.ailang in root directory
# - Library.RESP.ailang in Libraries/Library/

# 3. Build the server
python3 main.py redis_server.ailang

# 4. Run the server
./redis_server_exec

# Server is now running on port 6379
File Layout
ailang/
├── main.py                               # AILANG compiler
├── redis_server.ailang                   # Redis server code
├── redis_server_exec                     # Compiled binary (37KB)
├── Libraries/
│   └── Library/
│       └── Library.RESP.ailang          # RESP protocol library
├── test_ailang_redis.sh                 # Test suite
└── test_perf.py                          # Performance test
Testing
bash# Basic test
redis-cli -p 6379 PING
# Should return: PONG

# Full test suite
chmod +x test_ailang_redis.sh
./test_ailang_redis.sh

# Performance benchmark
python3 test_perf.py
# Should show: ~0.08ms per PING
Troubleshooting
If compilation fails:

Ensure Library.RESP.ailang is in Libraries/Library/ directory
Check that you have Python 3.x installed
Verify gcc is available (gcc --version)

If server won't start:

Check port 6379 is free (lsof -i :6379)
Ensure binary has execute permissions (chmod +x redis_server_exec)

Supported Redis Commands
PING, SET, GET, EXISTS, DEL, INCR, DECR, APPEND, STRLEN, ECHO, INFO, CONFIG, SELECT, FLUSHDB, DBSIZE, QUIT
